                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                        <locus target="#iv(erso) #1r" facs="002 004">Fols. iv(erso), 1r</locus>
                      <desc type="Asmat">Asmat prayer for help in learning</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                        <locus target="#ir(ecto) #1v #151r #151v" facs="001 005 154 155">Fols. ir(ecto), 1v, 151r, 151v</locus>
                      <desc>Blank except for scrawls and pen trials</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                        <locus target="#117r" facs="120">f. 117r, bottom three lines, continued on</locus>
                        <locus target="#136r" facs="139">f. 136r, bottom five lines</locus>
                      <desc>
                      <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ይቤሉ፡ አበዊነ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ እለ፡ አርአዮሙ፡ ኅቡአተ፡ ምሥጢራቲሁ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላኮሙ፡ ወከመዝ፡ ውእቱ፡ ፍሬሁ፡ ለ፩፡ መዝሙረ፡ ዳዊት፡ ፺፼ወ፷፻፡ ወዘንተሰ፡ እለ፡
                      ይዜ <locus target="#136" facs="139">fol. 136</locus> ምሩ፡ በአንብዕ፡ ወበፈሪሃ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወበሠናይ፡ መልእክት፡ ዘይጼሊ፡ በቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ነጐርጓር፡ ፳፻፼፲፻፡ በምሥራቅ፡ ፳፻፼፲፻፡ በምዕራብ፡ በሰሜን፡ ወበደቡብ፡ ከማሁ፡ ይከውን፡ ፍሬሁ፡ ይቤሉ። ወካዕበ፡ ይቤሉ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሰጊድ፡ ፷፼፡ ፍሬሁ፡</foreign>
                      “Our holy fathers to whom God, their creator, revealed hidden mysteries, said, ‘the (spiritual) fruit of one psalm is 106,000.’”
                      “And those who sing with tears and the fear of God and with good intent and who pray in the church without complaining
                      [will have spiritual fruit in the quantities of] 2,000 times 10,000 in the East, 2,000 times 10,000 in the West, and the same for North and South.
                      And also they said, ‘the fruit of one bow is 60,000.’”</q></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a3">
                        <locus target="#150v" facs="154">Fol. 150v</locus>
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of later ownership</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                        <locus target="#25v #50v #52v #53r #90r" facs="029 054 056 093">Fols. 25v, 50v, 52v, 53r, 90r</locus>
                      <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                        <locus target="#50r #75r #103v #132v" facs="053 078 107 136">Fols. 50r, 75r, 103v, 132v</locus>)
                        <desc>lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                        </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                        <locus target="#10v #131r" facs="014 134">Fols. 10v, 131r</locus>
                        <desc>e.g., text has been removed</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                        <locus target="#2r #3v #7r" facs="005 007 010">Fols. 2r, 3v, 7r</locus>)
                      <desc>
                      e.g., the scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate
                      aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line
                      of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto
                      the next line</desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
